// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/preprocess/p04/pass.test — P4 `#if` integer evaluation per
// `docs/spec/nsl_pp.ebnf` §2.3 + §3 and the contract topic table in
// `specs/002-m1-lex-preprocess/contracts/preprocessor-seam.contract.md`.
//
// Topic per the table: `#if 2+3 > 0` selects then-branch.
//
// P4 truth test: a `#if <expr>` evaluates `<expr>` to a `PPValue`
// (integer or real) per the helper-evaluator semantics; the truth
// test is "non-zero" on either kind. **No string comparison** —
// `#ifdef` is the symbol-presence form.
//
// This fixture exercises:
//   * additive arithmetic (`2+3`) in an `#if` expression;
//   * relational comparison (`> 0`) producing a 1/0 truth value;
//   * `#if` ↔ `#else` ↔ `#endif` pairing (covered more fully in P9).
//
// Pass shape (then-branch selected; the `tk_identifier then_taken`
// is what reaches the seam, NOT `else_taken`):
//   #if 2+3 > 0
//   then_taken
//   #else
//   else_taken
//   #endif
//
// Tasks.md T040: pass-only — fail-cases are covered by P9
// (mismatched conditional).
//
// **RED state**: against the unchanged Phase-3 tree the lexer sees
// `#if 2+3 > 0` literally and tokenizes `#`/`if`/`2`/`+`/`3` etc.;
// no branch is selected. Phase-4's `PPExpression` evaluator turns
// it green.

// RUN: echo '#if 2+3 > 0'   >  %t.nsl
// RUN: echo 'then_taken'    >> %t.nsl
// RUN: echo '#else'         >> %t.nsl
// RUN: echo 'else_taken'    >> %t.nsl
// RUN: echo '#endif'        >> %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=tokens %t.nsl | FileCheck %s

// CHECK:     tk_identifier{{[ \t]+}}then_taken
// CHECK:     tk_eof
// CHECK-NOT: tk_identifier{{[ \t]+}}else_taken
